----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The purpose of this Python script is to process DWI headers in the Leave One Out / Leave Multiple Out pipeline.
For a LOO use it once, for LMO use it several times to remove as many direction as you want.

usage: text_file_processing.py [-h] [-v] [-i I] [-o O] [-dwi DWI] [-grad GRAD] [-sh SH] [-gn GN] [-dl DL] [-dwil DWIL]

default values to use if LOO : sh = 20, gn = 25, dl = 7, dwil = 17 if LMO put the corresponding gn

optional arguments:
  -h, --help     show this help message and exit
  -v, --verbose  output verbosity
  -i I           Input hearder file path
  -o O           Output modified header path
  -dwi DWI       Associated DWI to the modified header
  -grad GRAD     Gradient Direction to remove
  -sh SH         Header number of lines
  -gn GN         Number of input gradient directions
  -dl DL         Header line containing dimension of file
  -dwil DWIL     Header line containing dimension of file

